{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17652005","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17652005"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:31:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:31:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18502"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18502","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18502"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.21,0.11,0.21,0.32]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11231"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80131"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11231","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11231"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18502"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65408"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7091"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26054"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26374"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27380"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80131","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80131"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe venous drainage of the kidney follows a hierarchical pattern from small cortical vessels to larger collecting vessels.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct sequence of venous drainage from the renal cortex to the renal vein?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arcuate veins \u2192 stellate veins \u2192 interlobular veins \u2192 segmental veins","Interlobular veins \u2192 arcuate veins \u2192 stellate veins \u2192 segmental veins","Interlobular veins \u2192 stellate veins \u2192 arcuate veins \u2192 segmental veins","Stellate veins \u2192 arcuate veins \u2192 interlobular veins \u2192 segmental veins","Stellate veins \u2192 interlobular veins \u2192 arcuate veins \u2192 segmental veins"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence of venous drainage in the kidney is \u003Cstrong\u003Estellate veins \u2192 interlobular veins \u2192 arcuate veins \u2192 segmental veins\u003C/strong\u003E. Blood from the renal cortex first drains into stellate veins, which are small vessels in the superficial cortex. These drain into interlobular veins that run perpendicular to the kidney surface. The interlobular veins then empty into arcuate veins at the corticomedullary junction. Finally, the arcuate veins drain into segmental veins that merge to form the renal vein.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The renal veins drain blood from the kidneys into the inferior vena cava.","The venous drainage of the kidney begins with stellate veins in the cortex that drain into progressively larger vessels.","Arcuate veins are located at the corticomedullary junction and receive blood from interlobular veins before draining into segmental veins."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65408"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18502"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65408","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65408"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T17:19:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T17:19:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11231"}},"conten